# AANAND AB — FLOATING ISLANDS PORTFOLIO
## Project Context
This is a cinematic portfolio website for Aanand AB, Junior Software Engineer at Spectra Solutions,
B.Tech Computer Science, University of Kerala.

## Core Mechanic — Three Layers
LAYER 1 (Hero): Sketchfab iframe embed — renders "Floating Island - Forgotten Shrine" 3D model with autospin. Full viewport hero section.
LAYER 2 (zIndex 2): Canvas element drawing 240 sequential JPG frames — scrollProgress maps to frame index. Scroll scrubs the flythrough.
LAYER 3 (zIndex 5): Fixed R3F Canvas — robot.glb companion that follows scroll, pointer-events:none.
LAYER 4 (zIndex 10+): HTML overlays — glassmorphism island cards, HUD, CLI, drawers.

## Assets
- public/frames/ezgif-frame-001.jpg through ezgif-frame-240.jpg — 240 sequential flythrough frames
- public/models/robot.glb — Flying robot companion (from robot_idle_animated.glb, 6.5MB)
- Sketchfab embed: https://sketchfab.com/models/43be02c79a1c4092b774bacda18b2f34/embed (Floating Island - Forgotten Shrine)
  CC-BY-4.0 license by Yosapat Panutyotin — credit required in footer

## Tech Stack
- React 18 + Vite
- @react-three/fiber + @react-three/drei + three — for robot.glb ONLY (RobotCompanion component)
- Lenis (@studio-freight/lenis) for smooth scroll
- GSAP + ScrollTrigger for scroll-to-frame mapping
- Framer Motion for HTML UI animations
- Zustand for global state (scrollProgress, drawerOpen, cliOpen, easterEggActive, activeIsland)
- Vanilla CSS for styling

## Frame Scrubbing (not video scrubbing)
- 240 JPG frames preloaded as Image objects on mount
- Canvas element draws frames via requestAnimationFrame
- ScrollTrigger onUpdate: frameIndex = Math.floor(progress * 239)
- Loading overlay shows progress bar while frames load
- Total scroll distance: 800vh

## Island → Project Mapping (frame-based timestamps)
Frame ~24-60  (progress 0.10-0.25) → CafePOSPro     screenPos: {x:'50%', y:'58%'}
Frame ~66-102 (progress 0.275-0.425) → Theyyam App   screenPos: {x:'28%', y:'45%'}
Frame ~105-144 (progress 0.44-0.60) → Knightly Web3  screenPos: {x:'68%', y:'50%'}
Frame ~156-198 (progress 0.65-0.825) → Evently        screenPos: {x:'50%', y:'48%'}
Frame ~204-240 (progress 0.85-1.0) → Bytebot AI      screenPos: {x:'38%', y:'40%'}

## Flying Robot Behaviour
- Rendered in its own fixed R3F Canvas, pointer-events:none, z-index:5
- Loads public/models/robot.glb (has idle animation)
- Waypoints array maps scrollProgress (0–1) to 3D positions + rotation
- Speech bubbles via Drei Html appear when robot arrives at each island zone
- Reacts to events: drawerOpen → spin. cliOpen → fly to screen-left. easterEggActive → celebrate

## File Structure
src/components/ — RobotCompanion.jsx (fixed R3F canvas with robot.glb)
src/sections/   — HeroScene.jsx (Sketchfab embed hero), HeroScene.css
src/store/      — portfolioStore.js (Zustand)
src/data/       — islands.js
src/App.jsx     — Root: Lenis, VideoScrollWorld (canvas frame scrub), ContactSection

## Design Rules
- Glassmorphism cards: background rgba(5,10,20,0.75), backdrop-filter blur(20px)
- Accent colors per island: cyan #38bdf8, gold #fbbf24, purple #c084fc, pink #f472b6, green #34d399
- Font: Space Grotesk (headings), Inter (body), JetBrains Mono (code/labels)
- Body background: #03060f

